Which is your latest gadget? Our pair of Oppo smartphones. How do they help you as artistes? To be honest, we see a phone as a source of information, and as you know, information is power, whether in entertainment or business or, in our case, the entertainment business. What do you love about phones? The phones make it easy for us to create and access almost anything. From the applications to the browser and the camera for capturing those rare moments and sometimes even record music voice notes. What’s your worst gadget ever and why? We had earphones that for some reason, wouldn’t work when you need them to. Music has always been the catch to the soul and this pair of earphones used to irritate. Which is your most expensive gadget and how much did it cost? A laptop that cost us just above Sh50,000. Which gadget do you use the most and why? Our phones mostly, because we are trying everything to connect our music to as many people as possible and have our brand extensively known to the outside world. Which app do you use most on your phone and why? The notepad. Since most of the times we don’t carry books, we type lyrics down on this app for easy access later. What would you be if you were a gadget? We would be anything that creates opportunities for people to be knowledgeable of the Bible. The gadget you can’t live without and why? If the Bible were a gadget, then that would be it because that’s our guide to life. If you were to upgrade one of your gadgets, what would you opt for and why? Our laptops since we need better performance and convenience for the kind of jobs we do. We need one with more storage space and fast functionality. The gadget you always wish you had? A MacBook or an iPhone.